<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h3>Patient Dashboard</h3>
    <p>As a Clinician, you have the ability to view all entries provided by your Patients.
      These entries are visualized into charts, trends, Key Performance Indicators (KPI's) and graphs.
      <br>By default, Patient Dashboard charts display entries for the <b>past 2 weeks</b>.  To adjust the timeframe, simply use the Datepicker in the upper left corner to select the desired date range.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h3>Observer Entries</h3>
    <p>Members can authorize family and friends to add entries to their records.  These entry options include "Apparent Mood", "Social Interaction" and a "Journal".
      As their Clinician, this provides you with visibility into their Mood as observed by others.
      <br><b>The Patient is not able to see Observer Entries</b>.  This is so that Observers provide honest and open feedback without fear of upsetting the Patient.
    </p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h3>Collaborative Treatment</h3>
    <p>Share important information that the patients' other Clinicians should be aware of.  This communication is easily done within Faro and removes the
      coordination and documentation handoffs typically present with collaborative treatment.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

